{"text": "## Make sure your water is safe\n\n\n Always look for announcements from local officials to find out if there is a local water advisory They will tell you if there are germs or chemicals in the water and what actions you should take.\n\n If you get water from a well and think it may be contaminated from floodwaters or another source, contact your local health department for advice on inspecting and disinfecting your well.\n\n Boil water for 1 minute if local officials say you need to boil it. This is enough time to kill germs in the water. Start counting when the water comes to a constant boil. Let the water cool before drinking.\n\n Use bottled water or another supply of safe water until you know your tap water is safe.", "embedding": [0.035207447, 0.0010625947, -0.14847377, -0.0010602452, 0.07728251, 0.022825236, 0.020520119, 0.019520922, 0.06805972, -0.04409027, -0.016642502, 0.063625656, 0.048907716, 0.031562127, -0.044355396, -0.029215671, -0.024649397, -0.08617116, 0.027204493, 0.027733382, -0.07245896, -0.047415633, -0.011384959, -0.028235365, 0.012995072, -0.013224388, 0.002016991, 0.070445456, 0.02430342, -0.014085605, -0.028445447, 0.00040573537, -0.042397644, -0.06757395, -0.030053623, -0.12880619, 0.020393992, 0.0018241383, 0.05158655, -0.015652403, 0.092524506, 0.01871855, 0.055628825, -0.077335075, 0.02786506, 0.039732892, 0.05813949, 0.0022686787, 0.045680553, -0.08363902, 0.035502754, -0.06038471, -0.06634886, 0.0022808728, 0.019401234, 0.039635632, 0.0025453896, -0.008883795, 0.046111844, -0.0125012705, 0.09435405, 0.07367059, -0.03580189, 0.047883693, 0.024230443, -0.009981553, -0.08782206, 0.056967005, 0.022727055, 0.061463803, 0.024579503, -0.03181771, 0.049706243, 0.0026578722, -0.03404495, 0.015427748, -0.021793442, 0.029183602, 0.010419683, 0.0198628, 0.051911946, 0.002773214, 0.07943246, -0.017869452, 0.019443111, 0.011255323, -0.036787223, -0.027220348, 0.023745697, 0.064208925, -0.008075604, -0.016699696, 0.0012546054, 0.083129585